h1. test

h2. Purpose

Executes the Grails tests via the built in test runner in Grails.

h3. Description

Calls the @test-app@ Grails script. By default passes no arguments, which results in all test phases and types
being executed.

Select specific tests to execute:

{code}
$ gradle test -Dtest.single="Foo"
{code}

Value of @test.single@ is passed as a Grails argument which utilizes Grails's pattern matching for which tests will
be executed.